The organic–inorganic hybrid perovskite materials have a typical ABX3 perovskite structure (Fig. 2a) [36]. The A site is monovalent cation such as methylammonium (MA+), formamidinium (FA+) and Cs+, B site is divalent cation such as Pb2+ and Sn2+, and X site is halide ion such as I−, Br− and Cl−. In the ABX3 perovskite structure, the A and B cations occupy the corner and center of the cubic unit cell, respectively, while the X anion locates at the face-center. The formability and stability of this structure is commonly evaluated by tolerance factor t and octahedral factor μ, defined as:1t=rA+rX√2(rB+rX)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
